  "title": "ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborating with project managers to understand project requirements, specifications, and expectations</li><li>Participating in project planning and scheduling activities</li><li>Inspecting construction sites regularly to monitor progress and ensure compliance with design specifications</li><li>Implementing and maintaining quality control procedures to ensure the project meets industry standards and regulations</li><li>Conducting tests on construction materials to ensure they meet required standards</li><li>Collaborating with architects, engineers, and other professionals to coordinate activities and resolve design issues</li><li>Provide technical solutions to problems encountered during the construction process</li><li>Efficiently managing resources, including labour, materials, and equipment</li><li>Implementing and enforcing safety protocols to ensure a safe working environment</li><li>Conducting regular safety inspections and addressing any issues promptly</li><li>Maintaining accurate and up-to-date project documentation, including daily reports, progress reports, and as-built drawings</li><li>Keeping records of materials used, labor hours, and equipment usage</li><li>Identifying and resolving construction-related issues and challenges as they arise</li><li>Providing regular updates to project stakeholders on progress, challenges, and milestones</li><li>Undertake any other duties assigned by management from time to time</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering, Construction Project Management or a related field</li><li>Experienced in engineering or site engineering in construction industry</li><li>Strong knowledge of construction methods, materials, and processes.</li><li>Familiarity with relevant construction codes, regulations, and safety standards.</li><li>Proficiency in using construction management software and tools.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Problem-solving skills to address unexpected challenges.</li><li>Attention to detail and a commitment to quality.</li><li>Able to multi-task and work under tight schedules</li><li>Strong negotiation and problem-solving skills</li><li>Able to face challenging tasks and meet high standards and deadlines</li><li>Able to attend to emergency call due to project and works needs beyond office hours</li><li>6 working days</li></ul>",
